# dm-verity prototype configuration.
#
# Read by vhdbuilder/packer/dmverity-prototype/install.sh during the
# AgentBaker AzureLinux 3 Packer build. To disable the prototype, set both
# URLs to empty strings; install.sh becomes a hard no-op and the VHD is
# identical to a stock build.
#
# Variables:
#   DMVERITY_RPM_URL    Anonymous-access URL to the patched containerd2 RPM
#                       built from steamboat/local-vm-scripts/build-rpm.sh
#                       containing the snapshotter signature handler
#                       (containerd pkg/snapshotters/signatures.go). As of
#                       2.0.1-3003 the RPM also ships a systemd drop-in
#                       (/etc/systemd/system/containerd.service.d/dmverity-overlay.conf)
#                       that re-overlays /usr/share/containerd2/config.toml
#                       onto /etc/containerd/config.toml on every containerd
#                       start, so AKS CSE's bootstrap-time clobber doesn't
#                       defeat the dm-verity config. Earlier 2.0.1-3001
#                       shipped the config + kernel-modules-load.d entry +
#                       Requires: erofs-utils / veritysetup -- no out-of-band
#                       wiring needed here.
#   DMVERITY_KERNEL_RPM_URL
#                       Anonymous-access URL to the patched Azure Linux 3
#                       kernel RPM (azurelinux@dadelan/kernel-update,
#                       Release: 99.osguard1%{?dist}). Bakes the OS Guard CA
#                       into CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRUSTED_KEYS so dm-verity layer
#                       signatures are verified out of .builtin_trusted_keys
#                       at boot without runtime keyctl enrollment. Installed
#                       by full file path so tdnf does NOT resolve from any
#                       repo (our 99.osguard1 Release outranks any realistic
#                       upstream patch release at the same Version, but a
#                       hypothetical upstream Version bump would silently
#                       win via repo resolution -- file-path install makes
#                       that impossible). Leave empty to keep the stock kernel
#                       and rely solely on the userspace keyring-load fallback.
#   DMVERITY_CERT_URL   Anonymous-access URL to the PEM-encoded OS Guard
#                       signer CA. With the patched kernel this file is only
#                       useful for userspace verifiers (e.g. `notation verify`)
#                       and as a fallback for non-osguard kernels via the
#                       aks-dmverity-keyring.service unit.
#   DMVERITY_RPM_SHA256
#   DMVERITY_KERNEL_RPM_SHA256
#   DMVERITY_CERT_SHA256
#                       Optional integrity pins; verified after download.
#
# WARNING: kataccstorage public access must be enabled before the VHD
# build runs and disabled afterward. See ../README.md for the
# `az storage account update --allow-blob-public-access true|false` toggle.
DMVERITY_RPM_URL=https://kataccstorage.blob.core.windows.net/aks-rpms/containerd2-2.0.1-3004.azl3.x86_64.rpm
DMVERITY_KERNEL_RPM_URL=https://kataccstorage.blob.core.windows.net/aks-rpms/kernel-6.6.139.1-99.osguard1.azl3.x86_64.rpm
DMVERITY_CERT_URL=https://kataccstorage.blob.core.windows.net/aks-rpms/osguard-signer-ca.pem
DMVERITY_RPM_SHA256=41fb18f0a06dca1abb96b9c2f73a021f6ee235ad7245e9e5608bf4892fa9382e
DMVERITY_KERNEL_RPM_SHA256=b43301c5b2fc0cc4951fecdb651e6dadbdf524d60f5944201804142706ff6317
DMVERITY_CERT_SHA256=d33ea66794030396aca27e039715dbab4e15ccf5530fdf431f0ed7d05639afaa
